{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6cf081c3-d81f-4218-9e5c-7fd28900df5b","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_U7UIgCyuF6xN5g8ilfJCYG","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Explaining MTP exit code 8"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"tooluse_DluVHX7LSZkxs9g7FsmG4r","name":"view","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-4ad30f84d561491c9f5409ba21450209"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"view the file at /tmp/sv-4ad30f84d561491c9f5409ba21450209."}],"interactionId":"1323bc48-f152-40ee-b8ba-3ee6e7b4b43d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user migrated from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) and is hitting exit code 8 when test assemblies produce zero tests. This is a known behavioral difference between VSTest and MTP.\n\nIn MTP, exit code 8 means \"no tests were discovered/run.\" VSTest used to return exit code 0 in this case. This is a common issue when migrating to MTP, especially with conditional compilation that can result in zero tests in certain configurations.\n\nThe fix is to use the `--ignore-exit-code` option or set the `TESTINGPLATFORM_EXITCODE_IGNORE` environment variable to tell MTP to treat \"no tests found\" as a success.\n\n\nI'll give them a straightforward solution with the specific command or configuration they need to resolve this.","outputTokens":295,"requestId":"E3C5:AB6AD:1C8AC94:1F89BED:6A052121"},"id":"30f658da-6e81-4ae0-9cea-0ddbdac40ed3","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:11:04.912Z","parentId":"c1f3fac8-575c-41fb-b9f6-72787bafa057"}
