{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"51c85b0c-27b3-48c8-9709-0e733e67dbd7","content":"**Exit code 8** in Microsoft.Testing.Platform means \"zero tests discovered.\" VSTest returned 0 in this case, but MTP treats it as a failure by default.\n\n**Fix:** Tell MTP to ignore that exit code. Two options:\n\n### Option 1 – CLI flag (per invocation)\n```bash\ndotnet test --ignore-exit-code 8\n```\n\n### Option 2 – Environment variable (CI-wide)\n```bash\nexport TESTINGPLATFORM_EXITCODE_IGNORE=8\ndotnet test\n```\n\nYou can also combine multiple codes: `--ignore-exit-code \"8;2\"`.\n\n### Option 3 – In your project file (permanent)\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TestingPlatformExitCodeIgnore>8</TestingPlatformExitCodeIgnore>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nThis restores VSTest's behavior of treating \"no tests found\" as success, which is what you want for conditionally-compiled assemblies that legitimately produce zero tests on some configurations.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1323bc48-f152-40ee-b8ba-3ee6e7b4b43d","outputTokens":245,"requestId":"E3C5:AB6AD:1C8CA71:1F8BD4A:6A052128"},"id":"9dd68e80-b556-4b81-8371-753bb62d0acb","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:11:11.548Z","parentId":"280bd326-bf24-4a65-afb2-37aafefbaa1a"}
